{"slug": "oracle", "root": "oracle", "category": "divination", "gloss": "a mouthpiece of prophecy", "definition": "An oracle is a mouthpiece of prophecy — a shrine, a priestess, or the divine utterance itself. The word names both the speaker and the thing spoken.", "history": "Latin *oraculum*, from *orare*, 'to speak, to pray' — an oracle is a 'speaking-place,' the god's mouth (the same *orare* behind *orator* and *oration*). Greece's oracles, above all Delphi, were institutions of state, and the Sibyls their freelance cousins. Magic's Theros set (2013) drew directly on this world, and 'Oracle' recurs as a title for its blue seers.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Etymonline, s.v. oracle", "where": "Etymology reference"}, {"label": "H. W. Parke, Sibyls and Sibylline Prophecy in Classical Antiquity", "where": "Reference", "url": "https://www.routledge.com/Sibyls-and-Sibylline-Prophecy-in-Classical-Antiquity-Routledge-Revivals/Parke/p/book/9781138015869", "url_kind": "publisher", "abstract": "Parke traces the legendary Sibyls -- prophetic women in the ancient Mediterranean believed to deliver cryptic verse prophecies -- from their earliest appearances in Greek sources through their adoption by the Romans and, later, early Christians who reinterpreted their sayings as predictions of Christ."}], "commentary": null, "commentary_sources": [], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"origin": "Latin oraculum, from orare ‘to speak, pray’", "first": "late 14c.", "note": "An oracle is a ‘speaking-place’ or the speech itself — the god’s mouth. Same root as oration and orator.", "hook": "The god’s mouthpiece.", "lang": "Latin"}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 34, "oracle_total": 4, "in_flavor_cards": 34, "in_oracle_cards": 3, "name_match_count": 31, "by_variant": {"oracle": 32, "oracles": 6}, "first_year": 1997, "colors": {"G": 11, "W": 11, "R": 16, "C": 9, "U": 19, "B": 5}, "by_year": {"1997": 10, "1998": 1, "1999": 1, "2000": 1, "2003": 1, "2005": 1, "2008": 1, "2011": 1, "2013": 3, "2014": 3, "2015": 7, "2016": 1, "2017": 2, "2018": 3, "2019": 1, "2020": 7, "2021": 4, "2022": 2, "2023": 3, "2024": 2, "2025": 2, "2026": 6}}, "cards": [{"id": "cfb8a8cc-293a-4b78-8ae8-5bdbfb61f5a6", "name": "Oracle", "set": "PVAN", "set_name": "Vanguard Series", "released": "1997-05-01", "type_line": "Vanguard", "rarity": "rare", "colors": [], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/a/f/af5cc745-7072-4f7f-94eb-c7670cb498ff.jpg?1782755492", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/a/f/af5cc745-7072-4f7f-94eb-c7670cb498ff.jpg?1782755492", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/pvan/304/oracle?utm_source=api", "local": "img/oracle/cfb8a8cc-293a-4b78-8ae8-5bdbfb61f5a6.jpg"}, {"id": "367faa8c-617a-41a0-901c-f65106e86d56", "name": "Oracle en-Vec", "set": "TMP", "set_name": "Tempest", "released": "1997-10-14", "type_line": "Creature — Human Wizard", "rarity": "rare", "colors": ["W"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/c/c/cc538730-c46c-4e5f-bc1f-0efb7765086d.jpg?1782720998", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/c/c/cc538730-c46c-4e5f-bc1f-0efb7765086d.jpg?1782720998", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/tmp/31/oracle-en-vec?utm_source=api", "local": "img/oracle/367faa8c-617a-41a0-901c-f65106e86d56.jpg"}, {"id": "731113a2-1366-41a4-9a34-61400ab3aa92", "name": "Etched Oracle Avatar", "set": "PMOA", "set_name": "Magic Online Avatars", "released": "2003-01-01", "type_line": "Vanguard", "rarity": "rare", "colors": [], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/8/f/8fb54be2-b9c5-4433-a198-4b935979718a.jpg?1782754351", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/8/f/8fb54be2-b9c5-4433-a198-4b935979718a.jpg?1782754351", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/pmoa/44/etched-oracle-ava